{
  "texts": [
    "The results demonstrate that LPS triggers phosphorylation of P38 and ERK, and that LPS-triggered phosphorylation is suppressed by co-treatment with CT, SAA and SAB for p38 and all four SMMCs for ERK (Figures 6A-C).",
    "Furthermore, all four SMMCs reversed the LPS-induced elevation in FOS mRNA expression, while TIIA, CT and SAA reversed the LPSinduced elevation in JUN mRNA expression (Figures 6D, E).",
    "However, the effect of the SMMCs on the expression and/or phosphorylation of AKT1, RELA, NFKBIA, MAPK8, MAPK10, CTSK, and CCL5 could not be confirmed (data not shown).",
    "Collectively, the above results suggest that SMMCs can prevent LPS-triggered inflammation through inhibition of P38, ERK and AP-1 (FOS and JUN), which might explain the functions of Salvia miltiorrhiza in ameliorating inflammatory induction during endometritis.",
    "To confirm the predicted functions of all six SMMCs in modulating the Platelet activation pathway (Supplementary Figure S2), we performed Western blotting of SRC, αIIbβ3 and p-eNOS/eNOS expression in platelets from dairy cows."
  ]
}